<item>
            <title>[JCR-23] PersistentVersionManager contains grow-only cache</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-23</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>The PersistentVersionManager class contains a private HashMap &amp;quot;histories&amp;quot; which contains references to InternalVersionHistory objects. The bad thing about this cache is, that it only grows, but is not being managed to forget about &amp;quot;unused&amp;quot; histories. This is even badder, as the class has support for on-demand loading of version histories.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Example: A repository which is filled with 9350 nodes and 52813 properties grows this histories map to 1&amp;#39;222&amp;#39;030 (!) entries. In this concrete case, the VM allocates 213MB to the heap of which 41MB is referenced by the PersistentVersionManager.histories map.</description>
